{"cursor":"2904","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox company\n| name = Capitol Films logo = foundation = 1989 defunct = 2012 fate = Bankruptcy\n|location_city = Los Angeles |location_country = United States |industry =\nMotion pictures |divisions = |subsid = ThinkFilm }} 'Capitol Films' was a\nBritish film production and distribution company, founded in 1989. [http://www.companiesintheuk.co.uk/ltd/capitol-\nfilms Companies in the UK: Capitol Films Limied] Retrieved 2012-02-16 In\nJanuary 2006 it was sold to American Mobius Pictures, [http://www.linkedin.com/company/capitol-\nfilms LinkedIn: Capitol Films] Retrieved 2012-02-16 owned by entrepreneur\nand film producer David Bergstein, and placed it at the hub of his Pegasus\nStudios. In early 2010, David Bergstein's appointment as director for the\nBritish company was terminated and the company was placed in receivership -\n[http://www.companiesintheuk.co.uk/Company/AllDocuments/capitol-films Companies\nin the UK: All official legal documents for Capitol Films Limied] Retrieved 2012-02-\n16 as part of the collapse of Bergstein's empire. In October 2010 the US\nbranch of the company was forced into bankruptcy, [http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/federal-judge-places-\nthree-remaining-97825 The Hollywood Reporter February 9, 2011: Federal Judge\nPlaces Three Remaining David Bergstein Companies Into Bankruptcy] Retrieved 2012-02-\n16 and in January 2012 a group of creditors filed a proposal with a\nfederal bankruptcy court in Los Angeles to take over and liquidate five\ncompanies formerly controlled by David Bergstein, among them Capitol Films. [http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/thr-esq/david-bergstein-\nthinkfilm-capitol-bankruptcy-279309 The Hollywood Reporter January 9, 2012:\nCreditors, Guilds Move to Liquidate Five Former David Bergstein Companies]\nRetrieved 2012-02-16\n\nCapitol Films was involved in the production of some fifty films, among them [[A\nGood Man in Africa (film)|A Good Man